The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Bedi ropes in Jawagal Srinath
New Delhi: Former India Test cricketers Jawagal Srinath, Syed Kirmani, Erapalli Prasanna and Hanumant Singh will offer tips to young aspirants at a summer training camp to be held in Dharamshala from May 15 to June 30. The camp, to be organised by the Bishan Singh Bedi Cricket Coaching Trust (BBCCT), will be open to youngsters between the age-group of 15 and 20 years. Well have the experts who will join the camp at different periods, former Indian captain Bedi told reporters here today. Srinath has agreed to give a week to the camp, he said. A junior squad for England tour will also be picked from the camp, Bedi said. (PTI)  Copyright 
